PROGRAM 5:
Package shape;
class Shape {
    // Method to be overridden
    public void area() {
        System.out.println("Default area");
    }
}

// Derived class Circle
class Circle extends Shape {
    double radius;

    Circle(double r) {
        radius = r;
    }

    // Overriding area method
    @Override
    public void area() {
        double result = Math.PI * radius * radius;
        System.out.println("Area of Circle = " + result);
    }
}

// Derived class Rectangle
class Rectangle extends Shape {
    double length, width;

    Rectangle(double l, double w) {
        length = l;
        width = w;
    }

    // Overriding area method
    @Override
    public void area() {
        double result = length * width;
        System.out.println("Area of Rectangle = " + result);
    }
}

// Main class
  class Shapes {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Test cases

        // TC1: Circle with radius 5 → Area ≈ 78.5
        Shape s1 = new Circle(5);
        s1.area();

        // TC2: Rectangle 10x5 → Area = 50
        Shape s2 = new Rectangle(10, 5);
        s2.area();

        // TC3: Shape default → "Default area"
        Shape s3 = new Shape();
        s3.area();

        // TC4: Zero radius circle → Area = 0
        Shape s4 = new Circle(0);
        s4.area();

        // TC5: Rectangle with width 0 → Area = 0
        Shape s5 = new Rectangle(7, 0);
        s5.area();}}
OUTPUT:
Area of Circle = 78.53981633974483
Area of Rectangle = 50.0
Default area
Area of Circle = 0.0
Area of Rectangle = 0.0
RESULT:
inheritance implemented successfully;
area() works for each derived class(NOTE:ALL TEST CASES ARE VERIFIED IN ONE PROGRAM ITSELF)
